         <para>
            <para.body>Such examples demonstrate how easy it is to comprehend linear relationships and to work with them. In contrast, non-linear relationships can be counter-intuitive and much harder to work with. For example, the quadratic relationship between car speed and distance to break to a full stop can easily be the cause of accidents. For another example of the counter intuitive nature of non linear relationships I'll suggest a deal to you:</para.body>
